1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:11,500
<i> I understand.</i>

2
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:14,500
<i>We all want to solve the case,
right?</i>

3
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:15,700
<i> Are we okay?</i>

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:16,867
<i> We?</i>

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,067
<i> Daddy, can I look around?</i>

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,033
<i> You can.</i>

7
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,667
<i>This place is perfectly safe,
okay?</i>

8
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:22,933
<i> She's beautiful.</i>

9
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,667
<i>Is this the first time you saw
the Mayor's daughter?</i>

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,667
<i>Your toys are impressive,
Mister.</i>

11
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:27,967
<i> I can't choose.</i>

12
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>What people believe
is what they see.</i>

13
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,400
<i>What's this trick you're
playing, Joaquin?</i>

14
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>Do you want to show people
that we can get along?</i>

15
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:37,533
<i> When we were in showbiz,</i>

16
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:41,167
<i>you were always a worthy
and challenging opponent.</i>

17
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:44,167
<i>I guess,
I'll take that as a compliment.</i>

18
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:47,567
<i> Are you ready to play and win?</i>

19
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,100
<i> We're still missing one girl.</i>

20
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:52,067
<i> Bobby! Bobby will join.</i>

21
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,800
<i>Look at the opportunity,
Enriquez.</i>

22
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:57,167
<i> And the one drawn is....</i>

23
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:58,667
<i> Kalamansi!</i>

24
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:00,633
<i> Yes, kalamansi, kalamansi!</i>

25
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:02,267
<i> Yes, that's right, Kapitana!</i>

26
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,967
<i>Is that Sir Tonyo's girlfriend?</i>

27
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,633
<i>Oh my, that woman is a fighter!</i>

28
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:21,333
- Kapitana, they hugged!
- And they're hugging.

29
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:31,100
Congratulations,
Sir Tonyo and Ma'am Bobby!

30
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:36,067
Granddaughter,
congratulations!

31
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,067
Hey, Bobby, congratulations.
Sir Tonyo, congratulations!

32
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,233
Sir Tonyo, congratulations!

33
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,233
Thank you, Grandmother.

34
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:43,867
Can I call you a grandson?

35
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,667
Grandmother?

36
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:47,633
Of course, Grandmother.

37
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:49,533
I can.

38
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,367
<i> Raise your hands!</i>

39
00:02:20,267 --> 00:02:22,433
So what are you going
to do with the prize?

40
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:26,333
Well, Sir Tonyo and I haven't
discussed it yet.

41
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,900
Kapitana, the Mayor is here.

42
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,933
The program is about to begin.

43
00:02:32,067 --> 00:02:33,067
The Mayor is here.

44
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:38,300
- Boss Tonyo! Hey!
- The prize!

45
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:39,567
You said earlier you didn't want
to play.

46
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:43,433
- That's ours! Wait a minute.
- The Mayor is here too.

47
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:46,267
- The Mayor is here.
- The Mayor. Come on.

48
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,767
- Yes, let's calm down, okay?
- Let's go, my grandchild.

49
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:51,033
Amo, can we take a picture?

50
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:52,933
Sure. Mine, mine, mine.

51
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:56,367
- Let's take a selfie.
- Yes, okay.

52
00:02:58,767 --> 00:02:59,367
Okay.

53
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,567
Do I look good in that? Okay.

54
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,967
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

55
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,467
Don't forget me.

56
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,400
Dude.

57
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:09,633
What is it, Dude?

58
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,867
I was going to invite you
to the stage.

59
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,367
I'm going to give my police
officers an award

60
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:17,000
for rescuing my youngest, Dude.

61
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,200
Why not?

62
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,333
It's also nice for the people
of Calabari

63
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,467
to see that we're united.

64
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:28,133
Especially on this fiesta day,
right?

65
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:34,133
Sir, Grandmother just freshened
up.

66
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,200
By the way, Enriquez.

67
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,867
Later, when we're asked to give
a speech, you'll be in charge.

68
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:41,567
Oh my.

69
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:42,933
Why me, Sir?

70
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:45,467
Aren't you more senior than me?

71
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:48,567
That's right,
I'm more senior than you.

72
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,433
That's why you deliver the
speech later,

73
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:51,833
and that's an order.

74
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,967
You owe me a lot, Sir.

75
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:57,533
Just make a list.

76
00:03:58,567 --> 00:04:02,133
Sir, where is Lieutenant Dizon,
by the way?

77
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:04,867
That's right.

78
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:08,167
Wait, I'll call him.

79
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:12,500
Hey, Ma'am Bobby!

80
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,033
You look happy.

81
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:17,600
You know, you were great
earlier, right?

82
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:18,700
That's right, Ma'am Bobby.

83
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,767
Actually, I idolize you
for what you did earlier.

84
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:24,100
Oh my, what's with you?

85
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,567
I wasn't the only one
responsible for the win.

86
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:28,100
It was a team effort.

87
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:30,267
Hey, that's not what we're
saying.

88
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,433
You're thinking wrong, Bobby.
That's not it.

89
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:33,467
Why? What was that?

90
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,900
When you hugged Tonyo.
How was that, Mar?

91
00:04:36,033 --> 00:04:37,033
That's right.

92
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:40,667
You know, you're so simple.

93
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,967
Buy your moves were obvious.

94
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:44,333
- How was that? How?
- Like this. Tonyo!

95
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:46,967
You won't stop?

96
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,133
- Yeah, no.
- No.

97
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:50,067
Go upstairs!

98
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,267
Call Grandmother!

99
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,933
It's his fault,
he's so mischievous.

100
00:04:53,067 --> 00:04:55,067
We'll go this way first. Okay.
How was that again, Mar?

101
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:57,100
Like this. Tonyo!

102
00:04:58,467 --> 00:04:59,233
Let's go!

103
00:04:59,367 --> 00:05:00,233
Very bright.

104
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,767
In fairness,
you're really good at that.

105
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,267
Go ahead!

106
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,067
These people are so annoying.

107
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:09,433
They really don't want to stop!

108
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:32,100
Grandmother?

109
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:34,033
Grandmother, hurry up!

110
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:42,267
I know you liked our previous
performers!

111
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:47,700
And now, I know you're excited
about our main event!

112
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:51,667
So let's not prolong
this anymore.

113
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:59,700
Everybody, let us all welcome
Selena and the Queen Bees!

114
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:48,967
Before we continue our
celebration,

115
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:55,433
our beloved mayor is here
for an important announcement.

116
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:56,800
Let's give a round of applause,

117
00:07:56,933 --> 00:08:00,467
to Mayor Joaquin Guerrero
and his family.

118
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,700
Thank you!

119
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:18,200
How are you,
fellow countrymen?

120
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:19,700
Are you enjoying yourself?

121
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,033
Thank you, if that's the case.

122
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:25,433
That's what I want.

123
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:29,567
All I really want is for you
to be really happy.

124
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:31,833
Yes, by the way.

125
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:39,467
Today, we will have with us
my longtime friend and now,

126
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:44,900
my future political rival,
Victor Santiago.

127
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:57,200
I also want to call our
Kapitana, Kapitana Isang!

128
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:02,033
And the beautiful Selena.

129
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:15,800
I know many of you have won
prizes from the many games here.

130
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:17,867
But first of all,

131
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:23,633
I want to give an award to these
extraordinary people today.

132
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:28,967
They have rescued my youngest
who is now with us here, Faye.

133
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:36,633
We would like Lieutenant
Antonio Conde,

134
00:09:37,533 --> 00:09:39,867
Lieutenant Fred Dizon,

135
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:43,433
Patrolman Jake Noble,

136
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:46,933
and Sergeant Bobby Enriquez
to go to the stage.

137
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,167
Sir,

138
00:09:59,967 --> 00:10:01,467
let's go there.

139
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:26,533
For maintaining peace
and order here in Calabari,

140
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:30,433
we sincerely thank you.

141
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:52,233
Again, let's give them
a round of applause.

142
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:07,467
And now we can continue the fun!

143
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:09,933
Wait a minute!

144
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:11,133
Wait a minute.

145
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:18,567
Can I borrow the Mic?

146
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:19,100
Yes.

147
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,033
Happy fiesta to all of you!

148
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,233
You know,

149
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:33,300
I was really touched
by the Mayor's speech.

150
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:39,267
So I thought I'd add a little
reward for those four.

151
00:11:42,633 --> 00:11:43,700
Is that okay?

152
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:45,600
Wait, wait. No, no, no.

153
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:48,600
This is better, you don't seem
to be very happy.

154
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:50,967
Let's choose one person
from the audience

155
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,233
who will also receive
a little extra.

156
00:11:53,367 --> 00:11:54,467
Is that okay?

157
00:11:57,167 --> 00:12:00,400
Let's start with ten thousand!

158
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:05,767
Okay.

159
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,333
I'm easy to talk to.

160
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,900
Let's close it to twenty
thousand!

161
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:22,533
- Amo! Amo!
- Amo! Amo!

162
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:23,633
Get down!

163
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:33,767
Enriquez, backstage.

164
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:48,800
Hurry! Quick! Let's go! Here!

165
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:51,233
- Ouch.
- Let's go here.

166
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,567
Selena, are you okay?

167
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,367
- Okay, wait, wait! It hurts.
- Selena! Come on, let's go!

168
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,033
- Sorry.
- Let's go!

169
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:57,867
Are you okay?

170
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,567
I think Selena is the target.

171
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,667
Surround the perimeter.
The shooter is still there.

172
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,333
Come on!

173
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:03,167
Okay.

174
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:04,833
Sir, we can't stay long.
Let's go.

175
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:07,033
- Let's go, come on.
- Grandmother!

176
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:24,567
Here. Run, come on!
Hurry up! Here!

177
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:26,767
- Oh, wow, okay.
- So handsome.

178
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,067
Sir, you need help?

179
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,533
- Run for your life!
- Yes. There's an exit...

180
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:33,000
Hurry up!

181
00:13:36,367 --> 00:13:37,400
Mommy...

182
00:13:38,133 --> 00:13:39,400
Mommy...

183
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:42,533
Daddy, please let's go home!
I don't want to be here, please!

184
00:13:42,667 --> 00:13:44,567
Calm down. You're safe now.

185
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:47,700
- Please let's go home, okay?
- You're safe now, hija.

186
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:48,433
No!

187
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:50,233
Are you okay?

188
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:51,900
Shut up, Victor!

189
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,333
We know you did this!

190
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,600
When are you going to stop
bothering our family?

191
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:59,367
Mom, let's not blame Godfather
Victor right away.

192
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:03,067
Glen, your mom is right.

193
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,967
If I get shot,
who will benefit?

194
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:07,167
Wait.

195
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,067
Are you the target?

196
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:10,733
What if I'm the target?

197
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:12,200
Then, you're responsible
for that?

198
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:13,567
Don't turn the tables on me!

199
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,067
- Don't accuse me!
- Dad...

200
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,067
Godfather...

201
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,433
That's enough.

202
00:14:17,567 --> 00:14:21,133
Okay, let's just say I wasn't
the target of the shooting.

203
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:24,567
You did it to make me look bad
for people!

204
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,433
Prove your foolishness!

205
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:28,833
Amo, Mayor, excuse me.

206
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,733
None of you were the sniper's
target.

207
00:14:33,033 --> 00:14:34,067
Then who?

208
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:37,633
According to Lieutenant Conde,
the performer, Selena.

209
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,367
But now, she's safe.

210
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,133
They're looking for the sniper,
but it looks like he escaped.

211
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,333
Grandmother,
drink some water first.

212
00:14:56,433 --> 00:14:57,700
What happened?

213
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:01,200
Kapitana,
no one died or was hurt.

214
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,300
But because of what happened,

215
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:05,900
it's been decided to postpone
the festivities.

216
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:09,033
The events and games
will be held on another day.

217
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:14,767
And Kapitana, maybe, for now,
let's just go home.

218
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:18,367
Mar, Abdul, you take care
of Grandmother, okay?

219
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,800
Grandmother.

220
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:21,533
Why? Where are you going?

221
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:24,233
To the police station
I'll find out what happened.

222
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:26,300
Okay.

223
00:15:28,767 --> 00:15:30,367
- Be careful, my grandchild.
- Yes, Grandmother.

224
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,433
You guys take care
of Grandmother.

225
00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:32,967
Be careful, Bobby.

226
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:39,467
Who could have done this?

227
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:42,567
Don't spin it, pretending like
nothing happened.

228
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:45,400
And even if there was a shooting
incident still,

229
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:47,167
we're in control, okay?

230
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:48,667
You know what to do.

231
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,033
You take care of it.

232
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:50,933
Dad.

233
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:52,933
Excuse me.

234
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:53,800
Okay.

235
00:15:55,867 --> 00:15:57,667
I've sent Faye and Mom home.

236
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,667
Why?

237
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,400
Isn't there a photo opp later?

238
00:16:01,533 --> 00:16:02,700
But, Dad, you know why.

239
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:05,800
It was wrong of you to continue
the fiesta program.

240
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:06,967
You even gave free food.

241
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,200
That's right.

242
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:10,133
You just have to act natural

243
00:16:10,267 --> 00:16:13,567
so that people will feel
like nothing happened,

244
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,367
and that everything
is under control!

245
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:19,233
We can't let unfortunate
incidents dampen our spirit.

246
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:21,700
So that's it.

247
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:26,200
What if the shooter was just
hanging around there?

248
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:30,633
And then there was another
commotion and someone got hurt?

249
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:34,233
If that's what you believe,
then you should have gone home.

250
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:36,333
You're still loitering around.

251
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:40,467
Unless you're going to make
a scene to cause trouble...

252
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,300
Well, that's another story.

253
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:46,467
Sir, we've covered
the entire area,

254
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,833
but we didn't see anyone.

255
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:49,933
It looks like the sniper
has escaped.

256
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:52,300
Sir, I'm begging you,
please help me.

257
00:16:52,433 --> 00:16:54,067
Miss Selena,

258
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:57,300
do you know any other reason
why you're the target now?

259
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,733
None. I don't have any enemies.

260
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:02,233
Do you know who wanted
to do this to you

261
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:06,367
or do you have any idea who
wanted to kill you?

262
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,067
Is he connected to Sonny?

263
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:14,500
Ma'am Selena, before Sonny died,

264
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,733
did he even mention any
important information?

265
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:34,700
<i>Wait, where are you going?
Are you leaving?</i>

266
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,433
<i> It's late?</i>

267
00:17:37,567 --> 00:17:39,367
<i>What's that?
That's your Boss, right?</i>

268
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,867
<i> Your boss is demanding.</i>

269
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,367
<i> Go back to sleep.</i>

270
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,333
<i> Who is that? Tell me.</i>

271
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:51,400
<i>He has a lot of money
and he's powerful.</i>

272
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:53,467
<i> You don't need to know who.</i>

273
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,600
<i> What if you don't come back?</i>

274
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:57,633
<i>Who should I ask?
Who should I go to?</i>

275
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:00,233
<i>I'll also find out
who your Boss is.</i>

276
00:18:00,367 --> 00:18:02,800
<i>Whatever you find out,
just keep it to yourself.</i>

277
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:05,067
<i> Don't trust anyone,</i>

278
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:08,300
<i> especially the police.</i>

279
00:18:08,433 --> 00:18:10,500
<i>He has a lot of contacts inside.</i>

280
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,900
Nothing.

281
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,900
Sorry, I don't remember
anything.

282
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:21,567
Sir, maybe you can help me?

283
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,167
I'm scared.
I don't want to go home.

284
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:27,333
I can endorse you for witness
protection,

285
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:30,633
but you need to cooperate
with the ongoing investigation

286
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:32,200
of the San Isidro bank robbery

287
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:35,100
and the kidnapping of Mayor
Guerrero's daughter.

288
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:36,167
Okay, okay.

289
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:38,700
And you'll be taken
to a safe house.

290
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:41,233
Noble and Dizon will accompany
you.

291
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:49,867
Sir, Maybe Sir Tonyo can watch
over me.

292
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,467
I trust him more.
He's the one who saved me.

293
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,067
That's okay with me, Sir.

294
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,733
Chief, just the two of them?

295
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:02,267
We're a buddy system.

296
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,533
We need a female companion

297
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:08,900
because our under-protection
subject is female.

298
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:10,500
You're going, Enriquez.

299
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:19,467
Sergeant Enriquez and
Lieutenant Conde will take you

300
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,300
and accompany you
to the safehouse temporarily

301
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:26,533
until you are assigned official
escorts under witness protection

302
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:30,100
and you will be kept there while
the investigation continues.

303
00:19:30,267 --> 00:19:32,133
Okay. Thank you very much, Sir.

304
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:34,333
What about my clothes?

305
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:37,900
I don't have any toiletries
with me, Sir.

306
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:41,033
I can go get Ma'am Selena's
things.

307
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:43,867
Garcia, go with Robles.

308
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,167
- Okay.
- You should go.

309
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:46,900
Yes, Sir.

310
00:19:47,033 --> 00:19:47,533
Sir.

311
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:54,767
Enriquez, Conde, take care
of Miss Selena first.

312
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,600
I'll just call someone.

313
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:57,567
Yes, Sir.

314
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:09,800
Why, Miss Selena?

315
00:20:11,067 --> 00:20:12,067
Does something hurt?

316
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:15,833
It's my foot. I tripped earlier.

317
00:20:20,767 --> 00:20:21,867
Wait, let me look at it.

318
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:24,967
That's the one.

319
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,333
That, that, that, that!

320
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:31,467
Ouch, ouch! It hurts.

321
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,767
Looks like you need ice.
I'll just get some ice.

322
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,500
Sir, are you leaving?

323
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:36,733
Don't leave me.

324
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:40,233
Maybe Ma'am can just get some
ice.

325
00:20:41,733 --> 00:20:43,967
Okay, I'll get some ice.

326
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,233
Wait.

327
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,333
Fussy...

328
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:55,133
Ouch, ouch, it hurts.

329
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:56,567
Help me.

330
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:57,833
She's pissing me off!

331
00:20:58,767 --> 00:20:59,533
So fussy!

332
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:00,600
It's a good thing you only got
that.

333
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:02,667
It could have been worse.

334
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:09,633
She's so clumsy, wearing high
heels and can't walk properly.

335
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:14,733
Ma'am, are you okay?

336
00:21:14,867 --> 00:21:16,233
I'm okay.

337
00:21:16,367 --> 00:21:18,200
But why do you sound like you're
talking to the...

338
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:21,500
- I'm okay, Bautista!
- Okay.

339
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:22,900
Go ahead, go back there.

340
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:24,067
Okay.

341
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:36,100
Bautista?

342
00:21:36,233 --> 00:21:36,933
Yes.

343
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,133
Can I have that?

344
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:40,467
- But there's nothing left.
- I said can I have that?

345
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,200
You have so many reasons, right?

346
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:48,967
Robles, which one does Selena
like?

347
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:52,833
Let's take both.

348
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,567
Is there anything else
to cover up?

349
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:57,600
This?

350
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,867
It's the same.

351
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:03,267
It's like cheating.

352
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:06,933
Hey, what are you doing there?

353
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:09,933
No, I'm just fixing things.

354
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:11,767
I'm looking for the slippers.

355
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,667
Are you looking for the slippers
in the drawer?

356
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:17,500
The slippers, they're just
here on the floor under...

357
00:22:17,667 --> 00:22:18,467
nothing.

358
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,400
I saw something
in the living room.

359
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:22,433
Let me get it.

360
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:23,700
You finish this.

361
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:25,233
Okay, can you get it?

362
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:35,933
Hello, Boss.

363
00:22:37,467 --> 00:22:38,833
I'm at Sonny's house.

364
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,367
I still can't find the SD card.

365
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,100
You need to find that!

366
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:46,833
Did you know there's evidence
there about the museum robbery?

367
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:49,500
We're all going to be in trouble
including me!

368
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:53,167
I really feel like Selena
knows something, Boss.

369
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:55,300
Well, we should go after
that girl!

370
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:56,500
Where is she?

371
00:22:56,633 --> 00:22:58,233
We've got her at the precinct.

372
00:22:58,367 --> 00:23:00,900
We'll move her
to the safehouse later.

373
00:23:01,433 --> 00:23:02,633
I'll send someone.

374
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,033
She's already with two police
escorts.

375
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:07,800
Maybe you can just leave
those guys out.

376
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:11,033
Regan, are you giving me orders?

377
00:23:11,167 --> 00:23:13,133
I can't help it if they
interfere!

378
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:16,033
They will get involved
if they interfere!

379
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:34,667
Ouch, ouch, ouch.

380
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,367
- Here she is.
- Here.

381
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:46,033
Sir, I'll leave you.

382
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:47,100
Where are you going?

383
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:52,667
Just here, I'll just be here.

384
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,200
Just a little,
just a little more.

385
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:16,200
Hey! Hey!

386
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:17,467
What happened?

387
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,100
Our colleagues got into trouble
near the corner of Milagros.

388
00:24:20,233 --> 00:24:22,233
The man from SUV started
shooting.

389
00:24:22,367 --> 00:24:23,033
Junior is dead!

390
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,400
Let's go respond.

391
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:25,433
Hello?

392
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,867
Hello, Chief? I need backup.
I followed some kidnappers.

393
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,633
They kidnapped someone
in Calabari Townsquare

394
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:30,933
and it looks like I'm already
in their hideout.

395
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:32,333
We were kidnapped.

396
00:24:32,467 --> 00:24:34,400
But I don't like her!

397
00:24:34,533 --> 00:24:35,900
Do you know what I want?

398
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:37,567
For you to get jealous.

399
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:07,900
Hurry up!
